WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.680 --> 00:00:04.680
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington DC.

00:00:22.980 --> 00:00:25.320
&gt;&gt; Levon Avdoyan: You know, in my
nearly 40 years here at the Library

00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:31.150
of Congress, my favorite
words have become the last 21,

00:00:31.150 --> 00:00:34.170
welcome to the Vardanants
Day Arminian Lecture.

00:00:34.170 --> 00:00:36.590
This time the 21st lecture.

00:00:36.590 --> 00:00:38.730
I see many familiar faces.

00:00:38.730 --> 00:00:43.550
Some of whom I will acknowledge
a little later, in the beginning.

00:00:43.550 --> 00:00:48.440
But I see one who has been here
almost every year, not here.

00:00:48.440 --> 00:00:51.190
And I'd like to call the attention
to the fact that my sister,

00:00:51.190 --> 00:00:54.310
who has been extremely
supportive, Lynn Young,

00:00:54.310 --> 00:00:57.540 position:56%
was caught in the floods of Houston.

00:00:57.540 --> 00:00:59.180
Went through two shelters.

00:00:59.180 --> 00:01:04.710
And is at least safe and sound
with her daughter now in Denver.

00:01:04.710 --> 00:01:06.370
She's one of the lucky ones.

00:01:06.370 --> 00:01:09.280
So, I would personally like
to dedicate this event,

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:12.850
the 21st Vardanants Lecture
to all those suffering

00:01:12.850 --> 00:01:16.160
from this horrendous hurricane.

00:01:16.160 --> 00:01:20.720
Before I go any further, I
would like to introduce a friend

00:01:20.720 --> 00:01:25.180
and colleague and a great
supporter of the Armenian Programs

00:01:25.180 --> 00:01:29.350
and Collections at the Library
of Congress, Dr. Mary-Jane Deeb,

00:01:29.350 --> 00:01:33.510
Chief of the African and
Middle Eastern Division.

00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:40.930
[ Applause ]

00:01:40.930 --> 00:01:42.230
&gt;&gt; Mary-Jane Deeb: Thank you.

00:01:42.230 --> 00:01:43.530
Thank you, Levon.

00:01:43.530 --> 00:01:45.140
And good afternoon everyone.

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:48.470
And welcome to the Library of
Congress and to the African

00:01:48.470 --> 00:01:50.790
and Middle Eastern Division.

00:01:50.790 --> 00:01:53.500 position:56%
Thank you, Ambassador Hovhannissian.

00:01:53.500 --> 00:01:58.990
And thank you all for being here to
celebrate with us Vardanants Day.

00:01:58.990 --> 00:02:04.020
The 21st such celebration in one
of the longest running series

00:02:04.020 --> 00:02:07.800
of programs in the
Library's history.

00:02:07.800 --> 00:02:11.210
Many of you, as was mentioned,
have attended these programs

00:02:11.210 --> 00:02:15.700
over the years, organized
by Dr. Levon Avdoyan.

00:02:15.700 --> 00:02:20.610
The one and only Armenian
specialist at the Library.

00:02:20.610 --> 00:02:24.820
Never before him had there
been an Armenian specialist.

00:02:24.820 --> 00:02:31.260
But thanks to a generous grant
from Mrs. Margorie Dadian, in 1991,

00:02:31.260 --> 00:02:36.130
the Library established a position
for an Armenian specialist.

00:02:36.130 --> 00:02:40.360
And provided funds to build a
collection of Armenian books,

00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:44.160
serials, manuscripts, newspapers,

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:47.750
as well as expand the
collections in other formats.

00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:54.980
Such as, maps, photographs,
prints, films and much more.

00:02:54.980 --> 00:02:58.160
The fund, which exists to
promote Armenian collections,

00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:01.350
has been used very wisely by Levon.

00:03:01.350 --> 00:03:05.570
In the past two decades, he
has built this collection

00:03:05.570 --> 00:03:08.590
by increasing his items seven-fold.

00:03:08.590 --> 00:03:14.160
From an estimated six
or seven items in 1991,

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:18.070
to around 47,000 items today.

00:03:18.070 --> 00:03:22.130
He also used the funds to
create the first ever exhibit

00:03:22.130 --> 00:03:28.090
on the Armenian book in 2012,
entitled "To Know Wisdom

00:03:28.090 --> 00:03:31.230
and Instruction, the
Armenian Literary Tradition

00:03:31.230 --> 00:03:32.530
at the Library of Congress."

00:03:32.530 --> 00:03:37.240 position:56%
It was accompanied by an illustrated
catalogue, a book really,

00:03:37.240 --> 00:03:41.820
of the same title, on the Armenian
collections at the Library.

00:03:41.820 --> 00:03:45.850
The book, which Dr. Avdoyan
wrote, originally in English,

00:03:45.850 --> 00:03:48.610
was later translated into Armenian.

00:03:48.610 --> 00:03:52.910
And eventually, both versions
were published online.

00:03:52.910 --> 00:03:57.450
Dr. Avdoyan has not only focused on
developing the Armenian collection

00:03:57.450 --> 00:04:01.470
and having it preserved and
made accessible to readers.

00:04:01.470 --> 00:04:05.960
But has also organized numerous
programs around that collection.

00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:10.840
The best known as undoubtedly been
the long running annual Vardanants

00:04:10.840 --> 00:04:12.510
Day Series.

00:04:12.510 --> 00:04:18.850
Its goal is to present topics on
all aspects of Armenian history,

00:04:18.850 --> 00:04:22.830
culture, politics and society.

00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:25.640
In that, he has succeeded
beautifully.

00:04:25.640 --> 00:04:29.050
And you can go to our webpage
and find the webcast of each

00:04:29.050 --> 00:04:30.990
of the previous 20 programs.

00:04:30.990 --> 00:04:37.240
And today, once again, to
celebrate Vardanants Day,

00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:41.130
Levon has invited an
award-winning writer,

00:04:41.130 --> 00:04:45.370
whose work has received the
highest level of recognition.

00:04:45.370 --> 00:04:50.930
And who is participating in the
National Book Festival tomorrow.

00:04:50.930 --> 00:04:55.160
Although Chris Bohjalian is the
New York Times best seller author

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:59.030
of 19 novels, he is
here today to talk

00:04:59.030 --> 00:05:02.670
about another aspect
of his life and work.

00:05:02.670 --> 00:05:05.520
I will not say anymore, as
I know that Levon will want

00:05:05.520 --> 00:05:07.930
to introduce him more fully.

00:05:07.930 --> 00:05:10.490
So, now, Levon.

00:05:10.490 --> 00:05:12.290
Thank you.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:17.160
[ Applause ]

00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:20.900
&gt;&gt; Levon Avdoyan: If you listen
to Mary-Jane's introduction,

00:05:20.900 --> 00:05:23.830
you would think that this is
a one man show, but it isn't.

00:05:23.830 --> 00:05:27.010
I'm going to go through
that a little later.

00:05:27.010 --> 00:05:31.870
But we've been blessed with
many partners in the endeavor.

00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:34.800
And I pointed out that
the Armenian collections

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:39.510
