00:05:49.170 --> 00:05:53.740
I would like to introduce
to you the present holder

00:05:53.740 --> 00:05:55.690
of the Ambassadorship there.

00:05:55.690 --> 00:06:00.140
Who has one won my praise
and friendship for being one

00:06:00.140 --> 00:06:02.450
of the most energetic I have known.

00:06:02.450 --> 00:06:08.160
And so, please join me in
welcoming his Excellency Ambassador

00:06:08.160 --> 00:06:10.510
Grigor Hovhannissian.

00:06:10.510 --> 00:06:22.340
[ Applause ]

00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:23.640
&gt;&gt; Ambassador Grigor Hovhannissian:
Thank you very much Levon.

00:06:23.640 --> 00:06:25.620
That was a very generous
introduction.

00:06:25.620 --> 00:06:29.120
I'd like to reciprocate.

00:06:29.120 --> 00:06:32.280
Knowing you, having you in
Washington is a blessing

00:06:32.280 --> 00:06:36.140
for me personally and for the
Republic for the Armenian culture.

00:06:36.140 --> 00:06:38.860
I thank you for the work
you do all these years.

00:06:38.860 --> 00:06:42.030
And I can't stress it
enough how appreciative

00:06:42.030 --> 00:06:46.040
and grateful we are
for the work you do.

00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:50.020
And we cherish this
institution and cooperation

00:06:50.020 --> 00:06:51.610
with the Library of Congress.

00:06:51.610 --> 00:06:54.370
That has become one of
the true cultural bridges

00:06:54.370 --> 00:06:58.560
between Armenia and
the United States.

00:06:58.560 --> 00:07:05.630
A landmark event of which the
Vardanants Day invariably makes

00:07:05.630 --> 00:07:07.110
intellectual contributions

00:07:07.110 --> 00:07:09.650
to the Armenian culture,
to the civilization.

00:07:09.650 --> 00:07:14.290
Not to mention the massive impact
it makes on disseminating knowledge

00:07:14.290 --> 00:07:17.930
about our country and
Armenian civilization.

00:07:17.930 --> 00:07:23.290
I thank you very much Mrs. Deebs
dear compatriots, Ambassador Evans,

00:07:23.290 --> 00:07:29.240
great friend of Armenians
for being here today.

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:32.680
Today marks the beginning of --

00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:36.760
actually, in a way it's
a new year, you know.

00:07:36.760 --> 00:07:40.690
Because people are
back from vacation.

00:07:40.690 --> 00:07:46.120
September marks a beginning
to hard work for many of us.

00:07:46.120 --> 00:07:51.540
There's lots of challenges
ahead of us.

00:07:51.540 --> 00:07:53.350
You know, there's changes
in Armenia.

00:07:53.350 --> 00:07:55.130
There's changes in
the United States.

00:07:55.130 --> 00:07:57.750
But institutions like
the Library of Congress,

00:07:57.750 --> 00:08:00.620
the Cultural Institutions
activities ongoing,

00:08:00.620 --> 00:08:06.340
help us maintain the overall, you
know, the level of friendship.

00:08:06.340 --> 00:08:08.730
And commitment of both
countries, Armenia

00:08:08.730 --> 00:08:11.330
and the United States
have towards each other.

00:08:11.330 --> 00:08:13.740
I thank you all for all you do.

00:08:13.740 --> 00:08:19.900
And I'm very pleased that I'll be
witnessing an extraordinary lecture

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:21.650
