00:08:21.650 --> 00:08:23.420
A person who we already,

00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:26.480
in the Armenian world,
called varpet, master.

00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:30.020
Only a few of our big
writers, big artists,

00:08:30.020 --> 00:08:33.750
you know, deserve that title.

00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:36.630
He's -- he won that right already.

00:08:36.630 --> 00:08:40.730
And I'm very happy I'll be -- these
lectures happening on my watch.

00:08:40.730 --> 00:08:43.600
And I thank you, Levon,
for putting this together.

00:08:43.600 --> 00:08:46.550
And as a token of our appreciation,

00:08:46.550 --> 00:08:50.350
last year I promised I will
never be coming empty handed.

00:08:50.350 --> 00:08:55.510
And today I brought the 47,000
first book to your collection.

00:08:55.510 --> 00:08:59.040
[ Laughter and Applause ]

00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:04.640
Very much reminiscent
of the topic, you know,

00:09:04.640 --> 00:09:09.630
is the DNA Western Armenia
or Eastern Anatolia.

00:09:09.630 --> 00:09:16.440
An incredibly rich volume that
provides the before and after look

00:09:16.440 --> 00:09:20.780
at the cultural patrimony
of the Armenian civilization

00:09:20.780 --> 00:09:24.370
of what we commonly
call Western Armenia.

00:09:24.370 --> 00:09:25.670
Thank you very much.

00:09:25.670 --> 00:09:27.510
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:09:27.510 --> 00:09:37.070
[ Applause ]

