00:10:14.220 --> 00:10:16.440
We have Tomoro Ohanian
[assumed spelling]

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:18.650
and Jasmine Han [assumed
spelling] of Conservation,

00:10:18.650 --> 00:10:22.820
who have done so much to
actually preserve our materials.

00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:26.500
And it's really, we have
done a marvelous job here.

00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:27.950
We have members of the community.

00:10:27.950 --> 00:10:30.090
We have members from
Prints and Photographs.

00:10:30.090 --> 00:10:33.760
We have a lot of friends
here to listen to you, Chris.

00:10:33.760 --> 00:10:36.060
But about Chris.

00:10:38.840 --> 00:10:45.130
I have put a biography
of facts in the program.

00:10:45.130 --> 00:10:48.110
I don't want to go
through his numerous awards

00:10:48.110 --> 00:10:52.060
and what he has accomplished.

00:10:52.060 --> 00:10:58.050 position:56%
What I want to say, in a few words,
is that when I started graduate work

00:10:58.050 --> 00:11:04.440
at Columbia in 1968, my
colleagues, my fellow Armenians,

00:11:04.440 --> 00:11:08.470
were amused when I
said I have one index

00:11:08.470 --> 00:11:10.830
to whether a good --
a book is good or not.

00:11:10.830 --> 00:11:14.360
And I look in the index and if
it has Armenia in it, it's good.

00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:17.390
And if it doesn't have
Armenia in it, it doesn't.

00:11:17.390 --> 00:11:20.780
Many years ago, an Armenian
friend of mine said, well,

00:11:20.780 --> 00:11:23.080
what do you think of
Chris Bohjalian's novels?

00:11:23.080 --> 00:11:24.390
And I said, well, I don't know.

00:11:24.390 --> 00:11:25.860
I haven't read one.

00:11:25.860 --> 00:11:28.800
And I got "Secrets of Eden" out.

00:11:28.800 --> 00:11:32.110
And I didn't find Armenia in it.

00:11:32.110 --> 00:11:34.060
But I loved it.

00:11:34.060 --> 00:11:39.780
It was a quintessential
American novel.

00:11:39.780 --> 00:11:44.520
Excellent storytelling,
wonderful pros.

00:11:44.520 --> 00:11:47.490
A sense to it that
really intrigued me,

00:11:47.490 --> 00:11:52.010
that lead me to read a
few others at that time.

00:11:52.010 --> 00:11:56.520
And then, five years ago,
something miraculous happened

00:11:56.520 --> 00:11:58.090
to all of us in the community.

00:11:58.090 --> 00:12:02.600
And that is Chris authored a book
called "The Sandcastle Girls."

00:12:02.600 --> 00:12:06.070
The very personal account,
the very hard account

00:12:06.070 --> 00:12:08.130
to read for Armenian Americans.

00:12:08.130 --> 00:12:11.380
But a wonderful account
of the Armenian genocide.

00:12:11.380 --> 00:12:13.330
And I, at that point, met Chris

00:12:13.330 --> 00:12:16.500
for the first time and
I liked what I saw.

00:12:17.580 --> 00:12:21.100
I liked what I saw and felt
very friendly toward Chris.

00:12:21.100 --> 00:12:26.030
To the point that I, last year,
asked an embarrassing question.

00:12:26.030 --> 00:12:30.960
Which was, Chris, tell me, will
you ever write a humorous novel?

00:12:30.960 --> 00:12:35.260
To which and I have this e-mailed
response, "Oh, heavens no."

00:12:35.260 --> 00:12:38.840
"All my books are about
dread" [brief laughter].

00:12:39.920 --> 00:12:45.400
They may be about dread, but
they are all exquisitely written.

00:12:45.400 --> 00:12:47.630
They are all well thought out.

00:12:47.630 --> 00:12:50.950
I've read several since,
"The Guest Room," this year,

00:12:50.950 --> 00:12:52.810
which I urge you to read.

00:12:52.810 --> 00:12:56.620
Now, I don't know if I can say
that or not, but I am saying that.

00:12:56.620 --> 00:13:02.020
And I understand next March,
"The Flight Attendant,"

00:13:02.020 --> 00:13:05.900
his 20th novel will appear.

00:13:05.900 --> 00:13:08.850
Those of you who know me, know
that I am extremely interested

00:13:08.850 --> 00:13:11.980
in the question of identity.

00:13:11.980 --> 00:13:14.630
And so, when I thought of
identity in literature,

00:13:14.630 --> 00:13:18.760
there was only one name that I
could think of to address you.

00:13:18.760 --> 00:13:25.080
So, I asked Chris if he would talk
about the possible impact influence

00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:29.930
of ethnic identity on
literary creativity.

00:13:29.930 --> 00:13:32.760
He readily accepted.

00:13:32.760 --> 00:13:36.290
And so, ladies and
gentlemen, I ask you to join me

00:13:36.290 --> 00:13:41.900
in welcoming Chris Bohjalian, as he
talks about "Echoes of Anatolia."

00:13:41.900 --> 00:13:45.740
An Armenian American novelist
discovers his literary DNA

00:13:45.740 --> 00:13:48.510
at midlife.

00:13:48.510 --> 00:14:00.480
[ Applause ]

