00:14:32.060 --> 00:14:36.040
Because the last time I was
here, was indeed five years ago,

00:14:36.040 --> 00:14:39.990
for Levon's remarkable
curated exhibition,

00:14:39.990 --> 00:14:44.340
"To Know Wisdom and Instruction."

00:14:44.340 --> 00:14:52.130
It was profoundly meaningful to
see 500 years of Armenian printing.

00:14:52.130 --> 00:14:56.960
Five hundred years
of Armenian culture

00:14:56.960 --> 00:15:02.940
in this magnificent building
in our nations capitol.

00:15:02.940 --> 00:15:06.010
I know Levon as a friend.

00:15:06.010 --> 00:15:11.100
But I know he is also an
enormous gift to the Library

00:15:11.100 --> 00:15:14.610
of Congress, to Armenian Americans.

00:15:14.610 --> 00:15:17.100
And to Armenians around the world,

00:15:17.100 --> 00:15:24.260
for his magisterial work curating
a collection to remind people

00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:29.010
of our long venerated
magnificent history.

00:15:29.010 --> 00:15:31.750
Levon, thank you for
all that you do.

00:15:31.750 --> 00:15:35.220
It is a particular pleasure
to be with all of you today

00:15:35.220 --> 00:15:39.790
because I'm not on a book tour.

00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:41.920
Make no mistake, I like book tours.

00:15:41.920 --> 00:15:44.870
It wasn't all that long
ago that my sold briskly.

00:15:44.870 --> 00:15:49.040
But only among people
with my last name.

00:15:49.040 --> 00:15:51.380
I try never to lose
sight of that fact.

00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:52.790
Most people presume, however,

00:15:52.790 --> 00:15:54.810
that book tours are
unbelievable glamourous.

00:15:54.810 --> 00:15:58.620
You jet around the country and
you hang with Oprah and Katy

00:15:58.620 --> 00:16:02.260
and Terry Gross and sell
whole pallets of books.

00:16:02.260 --> 00:16:06.310
But the reality of most book
tours is this, by day 14,

00:16:06.310 --> 00:16:08.830
you will have been
on 17 regional jets.

00:16:08.830 --> 00:16:10.130
And you will have been reduced

00:16:10.130 --> 00:16:13.440
to wearing a strange man's
underwear [brief laughter].

00:16:13.440 --> 00:16:15.980
I wish I could say
I'm making that up.

00:16:15.980 --> 00:16:19.010
I am not. It really
happened to me on the

00:16:19.010 --> 00:16:20.940
"Secrets of Eden's" book tour.

00:16:20.940 --> 00:16:23.340
You see, what happens on a book
tour is that the publisher wants

00:16:23.340 --> 00:16:26.640
to get you to as many cities as
possible, as quickly as possible.

00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:28.380
So, you spend one night
in every city.

00:16:28.380 --> 00:16:29.920
Monday is Boston.

00:16:29.920 --> 00:16:31.220
Tuesday is New York.

00:16:31.220 --> 00:16:32.520
